article.headline: Hawaii 74, Louisiana Tech 50
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Bobby Nash scored 18 points to lead Hawaii to a 74-50 win over Louisiana Tech Saturday night at the Stan Sheriff Center. Matt Gibson and Dominic Waters each added 16 points for the Rainbow Warriors (14-10, 5-6 Western Athletic Conference). Trey McDowell led Louisiana Tech (7-17, 5-7 WAC) with 18 points. Hawaii closed out the first half on a 13-2 run to lead 40-28 at the break. Louisiana Tech pulled to within 11 twice in the second half, the last time with 9:51 remaining. But Hawaii responded with a 21-5 run to lead by as much as 27 with 4:36 left. Hawaii shot 12-of-20 from behind the arc, including 9-of-15 in the first half. Louisiana Tech shot a season-low 28.8 percent from the field.
